.TH "INCOMING-EXTRACTOR" "1" "Jul 07, 2026" "0.0.0" "incoming-extractor"
.SH NAME
incoming-extractor \- incoming-extractor v0.0.0
.sp
Extract and convert assets from the PC and Dreamcast versions of \fIIncoming\fP (Rage Software,
published by Interplay, 1998\-1999).
.sp
Given a PC disc (directory, ISO, or \fBDATA1.CAB\fP), a Dreamcast GDI, or a directory of already
extracted PC or GD\-ROM content, \fBincoming\-extractor\fP mirrors the source tree into an output
directory, converting the proprietary assets to open formats and copying everything else verbatim.
The source is never modified.
.SH INSTALLATION
.sp
Install from PyPI with your preferred tool:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pip install incoming\-extractor
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Or with \X'tty: link https://docs.astral.sh/uv/'\fI\%uv\fP\X'tty: link':
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
uv tool install incoming\-extractor
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
This installs three console scripts: \fBincoming\-extractor\fP (the main extractor) and the
\fI\%standalone utilities\fP \fBian2obj\fP and \fBextract\-pvr\-pack\fP\&.
.SS Prerequisites
.sp
Several conversions shell out to native helper programs. They are not bundled and must be available
on \fBPATH\fP (or pointed at with the matching \fB\-\-*\-path\fP option). See \fI\%Native tools\fP for the
full list and where to obtain each one. The extractor still runs without them; only the conversions
that need a given helper are skipped, and the affected files are copied verbatim instead.
.sp
You also need a copy of the game. Both the PC (Windows) and Sega Dreamcast releases are supported,
as is an installed copy such as the
\X'tty: link https://www.zoom-platform.com/product/incoming-trilogy'\fI\%Zoom Platform Incoming Trilogy\fP\X'tty: link'\&. See
\fI\%Usage\fP for the accepted source types.
.SH USAGE
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
incoming\-extractor \-\-output OUTPUT_DIR SOURCE
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The extractor mirrors \fBSOURCE\fP into \fBOUTPUT_DIR\fP: recognised assets are converted to open
formats and every other file is copied verbatim, preserving the original directory layout. The
source is never modified. See \fI\%Asset formats\fP for the complete list of what is converted.
.SS Source types
.sp
\fBSOURCE\fP may be any of the following:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
A \fBPC disc directory\fP containing \fBDATA1.CAB\fP (an InstallShield cabinet).
.IP \(bu 2
A \fBPC disc ISO\fP containing \fBDATA1.CAB\fP\&. The cabinet is first extracted from the ISO with
\fBisodump\fP or \fB7z\fP, then unpacked.
.IP \(bu 2
A \fB\(ga\(gaDATA1.CAB\(ga\(ga file\fP on its own.
.IP \(bu 2
A \fBDreamcast GDI\fP (a \fB\&.gdi\fP file with its track files beside it), unpacked with
\fBgdiextract\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
A \fBdirectory of already extracted\fP PC or GD\-ROM content.
.UNINDENT
.SS Installed copies
.sp
An installed copy works as the source too. Point at the game\(aqs directory, such as the
\fBIncoming 3DFX\fP folder of the
\X'tty: link https://www.zoom-platform.com/product/incoming-trilogy'\fI\%Zoom Platform Incoming Trilogy\fP\X'tty: link'
(\fB…/Incoming Trilogy/Incoming 3DFX\fP).
.sp
The \fIIncoming 3DFX\fP, \fIIncoming USA\fP, and \fIIncoming Subversion\fP (an expansion pack) titles share the
original engine and are supported. \fIIncoming Forces\fP uses a different engine and is \fBnot\fP
supported.
.SS Options
.sp
Pass \fB\-\-gdiextract\-path\fP, \fB\-\-spvr2png\-path\fP, or \fB\-\-unshield\-path\fP to point at the
\fI\%native tools\fP when they are not on \fBPATH\fP, and \fB\-\-debug\fP for verbose
logging.
.SS Command reference
.SS incoming\-extractor
.sp
Extract and convert Incoming assets from SOURCE into the output directory.
.sp
SOURCE may be a PC disc directory or ISO containing DATA1.CAB (or the DATA1.CAB itself), a
Dreamcast GDI file, or a directory of already extracted PC or GD\-ROM content. The source tree is
mirrored into the output directory: recognised assets are converted and every other file is
copied verbatim. The source is never modified.
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
incoming\-extractor [OPTIONS] SOURCE
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Options
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show the version and exit.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enable debug output.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-jobs <jobs>
Number of concurrent conversion jobs; defaults to the CPU count.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output <output>
\fBRequired\fP Output directory; the source tree is mirrored into it.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-gdiextract\-path <gdiextract_path>
Path to the gdiextract binary.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-spvr2png\-path <spvr2png_path>
Path to the spvr2png binary.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-unshield\-path <unshield_path>
Path to the unshield binary.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Arguments
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B SOURCE
Required argument
.UNINDENT
.SH UTILITIES
.sp
Alongside the main \fI\%incoming\-extractor\fP command, two standalone console scripts convert
a single asset without mirroring a whole source tree. They are installed with the package.
.SS ian2obj
.sp
Convert one model to Wavefront OBJ and MTL. Both the PC \fB\&.ian\fP mesh format and the Dreamcast
\fB*_M.BIN\fP model pack are accepted; the format is detected from the file name. A Dreamcast pack
needs its matching \fB*_ML.BIN\fP index beside it and writes one OBJ and MTL per contained object.
.sp
Textures are resolved from the game root, which is auto\-detected by walking up from the model (or
given explicitly with \fB\-\-game\-root\fP): the \fB\&.odl\fP plus \fB\&.ppm\fP files for a PC model, or the
level \fB*_T.PVR\fP pack for a Dreamcast model. Pass \fB\-\-no\-texture\fP to skip texture resolution. See
\fI\%Models and scenes\fP for the underlying formats.
.SS ian2obj
.sp
Convert an Incoming model MODEL to Wavefront OBJ and MTL in OUTDIR.
.sp
A PC \fB\&.ian\fP model yields a single OBJ and MTL. A Dreamcast \fB*_M.BIN\fP model pack yields one
OBJ and MTL per contained object under \fBOUTDIR/<model name>/\fP and needs the matching
\fB*_ML.BIN\fP index beside it. Each texture is resolved from the game root \-\- \fB\&.odl\fP plus
\fB\&.ppm\fP files for a PC model, or the level \fB*_T.PVR\fP pack (which requires \fBspvr2png\fP on
\fBPATH\fP) for a Dreamcast model \-\- and written next to the material, unless \fB\-\-no\-texture\fP is
given.
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
ian2obj [OPTIONS] MODEL OUTDIR
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Options
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-game\-root <game_root>
Game directory used to resolve textures; auto\-detected from MODEL if omitted.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-no\-texture
Do not resolve or write textures.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enable debug output.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Arguments
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B MODEL
Required argument
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B OUTDIR
Required argument
.UNINDENT
.SS extract\-pvr\-pack
.sp
Unpack a Dreamcast \fB*_T.PVR\fP texture pack. Each contained texture is written under
\fBOUTDIR/<pack name>/\fP as a separate \fB\&.pvr\fP file, or as a PNG with \fB\-\-png\fP (which requires
\fBspvr2png\fP). See \fI\%Textures\fP for the pack layout.
.SS extract\-pvr\-pack
.sp
Unpack an Incoming Dreamcast \fB*_T.PVR\fP texture pack PACK into OUTDIR.
.sp
This pack container is Dreamcast\-specific. Each contained texture is written under
\fBOUTDIR/<pack name>/\fP as a separate \fB\&.pvr\fP file, or as a PNG when \fB\-\-png\fP is given (which
requires \fBspvr2png\fP on \fBPATH\fP).
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
extract\-pvr\-pack [OPTIONS] PACK OUTDIR
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Options
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-png, \-\-no\-png
Convert the textures to PNG with spvr2png instead of writing raw PVR files.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enable debug output.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Arguments
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B PACK
Required argument
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B OUTDIR
Required argument
.UNINDENT
.SH NATIVE TOOLS
.sp
Some conversions shell out to native helper programs. Each must be on \fBPATH\fP or supplied with the
matching \fB\-\-*\-path\fP option. When a helper is missing, only the conversions that need it are
skipped and the affected files are copied verbatim.
.TS
