\X'tty: link https://sourceforge.net/projects/cdrtools/'\fI\%isodump\fP\X'tty: link' or \X'tty: link https://www.7-zip.org/'\fI\%7z\fP\X'tty: link', whichever
is found first on \fBPATH\fP\&.
.SH ASSET FORMATS
.sp
Status and notes for every asset format handled by \fBincoming\-extractor\fP\&. Two builds are covered:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBPC\fP — Windows, driven by \fBincoming.exe\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBDC\fP — Sega Dreamcast, driven by \fB1ST_READ.BIN\fP\&.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Many formats are shared between the two builds. Each conversion is reverse\-engineered to a fully
decoded, open output; where a format has no portable schema (or is already open) it is copied
verbatim instead.
.SS Legend
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
✅ \fBconverted\fP — decoded and re\-written in an open format.
.IP \(bu 2
📄 \fBcopied verbatim\fP — already open, or no portable schema, so the original is mirrored as\-is.
.IP \(bu 2
🚧 \fBbeing decoded\fP — partially understood; not yet converted.
.UNINDENT
.SS Format groups
.sp
The formats are grouped by subsystem:
.SS Disc containers
.sp
The outermost layer of each release is a disc container that holds every other asset. The extractor
unpacks these first, then walks the resulting tree. See \fI\%the legend\fP for the
status symbols.
.TS
