.SS PC: \fBDATA1.CAB\fP
.sp
The PC disc ships its files inside a single InstallShield cabinet, \fBDATA1.CAB\fP\&. The extractor
accepts the disc directory, the \fBDATA1.CAB\fP file directly, or a PC ISO that contains it. When
given an ISO, the cabinet is first extracted with \fBisodump\fP or \fB7z\fP (whichever is found on
\fBPATH\fP) and then unpacked with \fBunshield\fP\&.
.SS DC: GDI + tracks
.sp
The Dreamcast disc is distributed as a GDI: a \fB\&.gdi\fP text index alongside the raw track files. The
ISO 9660 file system on the data track is extracted with \fBgdiextract\fP, yielding the GD\-ROM
directory tree that the extractor then walks.
.sp
See \fI\%Native tools\fP for where to obtain \fBunshield\fP, \fBgdiextract\fP, \fBisodump\fP, and
\fB7z\fP\&.
