.SS PC: \fB\&.IAN\fP
.sp
A single mesh stored at several levels of detail; the converter reads the highest\-detail level
only. The \fB\&.ian\fP file carries no texture of its own. The referencing \fB\&.odl\fP pairs each mesh with
a \fB\&.ppm\fP texture (see \fI\%Textures\fP), which is resolved, converted to PNG, written beside the
model, and referenced from the generated material.
.SS DC: \fB*_M.BIN\fP and \fB*_ML.BIN\fP
.sp
A \fB*_M.BIN\fP is a \fBpack of many independent objects\fP — a level\(aqs models: terrain patches,
buildings, props, and vehicles. Its companion \fB*_ML.BIN\fP is the directory: an array of \fBuint32\fP
file offsets into the \fB*_M.BIN\fP, terminated by \fB0xFFFFFFFF\fP\&.
.sp
Each offset points at a 144\-byte object header. The active level\-of\-detail record (at +0x10) gives a
face count, a packed \fB(texture_index << 16) | vertex_count\fP word, and file offsets to a vertex
pool (40\-byte records: position, normal, and UV) and a triangle pool (16\-byte records). Non\-mesh
objects (sprites and placeholders) are detected by out\-of\-range pointers and skipped.
.sp
Each decodable object is written as its own \fB<stem>_<NNN>.obj\fP and \fB\&.mtl\fP in a directory named
after the source. The object\(aqs texture — the \fBtexture_index\fP sub\-texture of the level\(aqs
\fB*_T.PVR\fP pack (see \fI\%Textures\fP) — is extracted and written as a PNG beside the material.
.sp
The \fB*_ML.BIN\fP index itself is also converted to JSON (its offset count and offset list), which is
useful for inspecting the pack.
.SS Coordinate transform
.sp
\fIIncoming\fP uses a left\-handed coordinate system with up = \-Y; Wavefront OBJ is right\-handed with
up = +Y. Both model converters apply the same transform when emitting OBJ:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBNegating Y alone\fP performs the left\-to\-right\-handed conversion and the up flip in one step.
Because it is a single\-axis reflection, it also turns the game\(aqs clockwise\-front winding into
OBJ\(aqs counter\-clockwise\-front, so the winding is kept as written.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBTexture V is flipped\fP (\fB1 \- v\fP) to move from the game\(aqs top\-left texture origin to OBJ\(aqs
bottom\-left origin.
.UNINDENT
.sp
These transforms are recorded as comments at the top of every generated OBJ.
.SS Copied formats
.sp
\fB\&.MDL\fP, \fB\&.ODL\fP, and \fB\&.WDL\fP are plain\-text definition DSLs (physics and configuration, object
definitions, and world definitions, respectively). They are already human\-readable, so they are
copied verbatim. The \fB\&.odl\fP files are additionally \fIread\fP during conversion to resolve PC \fB\&.ian\fP
textures, but the files themselves are not modified.
.SS Audio and sound banks
.sp
See \fI\%the legend\fP for the status symbols.
