.TE
.SS DC: \fB\&.raw\fP (CDDA audio)
.sp
Red Book CDDA ripped verbatim: signed 16\-bit, 44100 Hz, stereo, interleaved, whole 2352\-byte
sectors, native little\-endian. Conversion is a straight RIFF/WAVE header wrap with \fBno byte\-swap\fP;
a proper rip is not swapped.
.SS DC: \fB\&.OSB\fP and \fB\&.MLT\fP (Manatee sound)
.sp
\fB\&.OSB\fP is a \fBSOSB\fP speech/SFX bank: a 16\-byte header, an offset table of \fBSOSP\fP voice records,
and each record holding packed AICA voice registers (sample start, length, 4\-bit ADPCM codec, and
pitch). Every record is decoded with the Yamaha/AICA ADPCM algorithm to signed 16\-bit mono PCM and
written as one WAV per record (22050 Hz in the shipped banks).
.sp
\fB\&.MLT\fP is a Sega \fBSMLT\fP multi\-unit container. Its 32\-byte\-per\-unit table (type, bank, AICA
address and size, file offset and size) is decoded to JSON.
.SS DC: \fBManatee.drv\fP
.sp
Sega\(aqs Manatee AICA sound\-driver program, uploaded to the audio chip at runtime. This is executable
