.SS \fBincoming_extractor.converters.models_dc\fP
.sp
Model converters: Incoming Dreamcast \fB*_M.BIN\fP / \fB*_ML.BIN\fP to OBJ, MTL, and JSON.
.sp
An \fB*_ML.BIN\fP is a directory of \fBuint32\fP file offsets into the matching \fB*_M.BIN\fP, terminated
by \fB0xFFFFFFFF\fP\&. Each offset points at a 144\-byte object header in the \fB*_M.BIN\fP; the active
level\-of\-detail record gives face and vertex counts plus file offsets to a vertex pool (40\-byte
records) and a triangle pool (16\-byte records). The high 16 bits of the count word are an index into
the level\(aqs \fB*_T.PVR\fP texture pack.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B incoming_extractor.converters.models_dc.mbin_to_obj(\fI\%source\fP: \X'tty: link https://docs.python.org/3/library/pathlib.html#pathlib.Path'\fI\%Path\fP\X'tty: link', \fI\%dest_dir\fP: \X'tty: link https://docs.python.org/3/library/pathlib.html#pathlib.Path'\fI\%Path\fP\X'tty: link') -> \X'tty: link https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#tuple'\fI\%tuple\fP\X'tty: link'[\X'tty: link https://docs.python.org/3/library/pathlib.html#pathlib.Path'\fI\%Path\fP\X'tty: link', \&...]
Convert an Incoming Dreamcast \fB*_M.BIN\fP model pack into one OBJ + MTL per object.
.sp
A \fB*_M.BIN\fP is a pack of many independent objects indexed by the matching \fB*_ML.BIN\fP\&. Each
decodable mesh object is written as its own \fB<stem>_<NNN>.obj\fP and \fB\&.mtl\fP in a directory
named after the source. Non\-mesh objects (sprites and placeholders) are skipped, and each
object\(aqs texture is extracted from the level \fB*_T.PVR\fP pack and referenced from its material.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
