.SS \fBincoming_extractor.converters.state\fP
.sp
State converters: Incoming save, config, and snapshot files to JSON.
.sp
The schemas are reverse\-engineered from the PC executable (\fBincoming.exe\fP). The configuration file
(\fB\&.cfg\fP) is a concatenation of fixed\-size blocks described by the game\(aqs internal save\-descriptor
table, so it is split into its named blocks, each decoded into a typed value (text, numeric arrays,
and the verified checksum). The snapshot files (\fB\&.sav\fP, \fB\&.xxx\fP, and \fB\&.lev\fP) are
\fBmemcpy\fP\-style images of a contiguous region of game globals, so a field table mapping each
global\(aqs offset, type, and name is applied. Every byte is decoded into a typed value: bytes not
covered by a known field
(gaps, large pools, and run\-time pointer tables) are emitted as \fBunknownAt_<offset>\fP arrays of
32\-bit words (or raw byte values when unaligned). Nothing is left as an opaque base64 blob.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B incoming_extractor.converters.state.cfg_to_json(\fI\%source\fP: Path, \fI\%dest_dir\fP: Path) -> Path
Convert an Incoming \fB\&.cfg\fP configuration file to JSON.
.sp
The file (\fBSaveGameConfigFile\fP) is a concatenation of fixed\-size blocks. Each block is decoded
into a human\-readable value: the build stamp and trailing buffers as text; the keybind block as
four control\-config pages of ten slots, each a DirectInput scancode with its key name; the
options block as the serial/modem connection settings (COM port, baud rate, stop bits, parity,
and flow control); the high\-score block as a list of tables of \fB{score, name}\fP entries; the
force\-feedback flag as a boolean; and the checksum as an object that recomputes and verifies it.
Nothing is left as an opaque blob.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Parameters
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B source : Path
The source \fB\&.cfg\fP file.
.TP
.B dest_dir : Path
The directory the JSON is written to.
.UNINDENT
.TP
.B Returns
The written JSON path.
.TP
.B Return type
Path
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
