.SH DEVELOPMENT
.sp
Set up a working tree with \X'tty: link https://docs.astral.sh/uv/'\fI\%uv\fP\X'tty: link' and Yarn:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
uv sync \-\-all\-groups \-\-all\-extras
yarn install
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Run the formatters and the quality\-assurance checks:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
yarn format
yarn qa
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fByarn qa\fP runs the type checks and linters; the test suite runs under
\X'tty: link https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/'\fI\%pytest\fP\X'tty: link' with full branch coverage. Both \fByarn format\fP and
\fByarn qa\fP must exit cleanly before committing.
.SS Documentation
.sp
The documentation is built with \X'tty: link https://www.sphinx-doc.org/'\fI\%Sphinx\fP\X'tty: link':
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
yarn gen\-docs
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The build runs with warnings treated as errors, so a new public module must be added to the
\fI\%API reference\fP reference (or, for a command, to \fI\%Utilities\fP) for the build to pass.
